      <p>These creatures feed primarily on carrion and offal, gathering heaps of the stuff in which to build nests and lay eggs. A <a href="ch74s03.html#MonstersVermin10">giant bombardier beetle</a> is about 6 feet long. <a href="ch74s03.html#MonstersVermin10">Giant bombardier beetles</a> normally attack only to defend themselves, their nests, or their eggs.</p>
